<abstract>

<para>
&kzen; is an application for the verification and repair of source files
using parity *.par2 and *.PAR2 files.
</para>

</abstract>

<keywordset>
<keyword>KDE</keyword>
<keyword>kdeutils</keyword>
<keyword>KZen</keyword>
<keyword>MTP</keyword>
</keywordset>

</bookinfo>

<chapter id="introduction">

<title>Introduction</title>

<para>
&kzen; is an applicationfor managing portable media players that use the MTP protocol. Please report any problems or feature requests as an issue on &homepage;
</para>

</chapter>

<chapter id="using-kzen">

<title>Using &kzen;</title>

<para>
<screenshot>
<screeninfo>Here's a screenshot of &kzen;</screeninfo>
	<mediaobject>
	  <imageobject>
	    <imagedata fileref="kzen.png" format="PNG"/>
	  </imageobject>
	  <textobject>
	    <phrase>Screenshot</phrase>
	  </textobject>
	</mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>

<para>
You can double click on any *.par2 or *.PAR2 file that you wish to load into KZen.
KZen will automatically open and proceed to load the recovery files.
Alternatively, you can open any PAR file via

<variablelist>
<varlistentry>
<term><menuchoice>
<guimenu>File</guimenu>
<guimenuitem>Open PAR2 File</guimenuitem>
</menuchoice></term>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

<para>
<screenshot>
<screeninfo>&kzen; after loading PAR2 files</screeninfo>
	<mediaobject>
	  <imageobject>
	    <imagedata fileref="kzen_loaded.png" format="PNG"/>
	  </imageobject>
	  <textobject>
	    <phrase>Screenshot</phrase>
	  </textobject>
	</mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>

<para>
Once loaded, KZen will proceed to verify and if neccessary repair any files that need repairing
if the "Automatically check" and "Automatically repair" options are enabled.
If they are not enabled, then the user will have to command KZen to carry out these steps
using the buttons in the main window.
</para>

<para>
<screenshot>
<screeninfo>&kzen; verifying source files</screeninfo>
	<mediaobject>
	  <imageobject>
	    <imagedata fileref="kzen_checking.png" format="PNG"/>
	  </imageobject>
	  <textobject>
	    <phrase>Screenshot</phrase>
	  </textobject>
	</mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>

<para>
If all source files pass verification &kzen; will report that all source files are correct.
</para>

<para>
<screenshot>
<screeninfo>&kzen; has verified the source files</screeninfo>
	<mediaobject>
	  <imageobject>
	    <imagedata fileref="kzen_all_correct.png" format="PNG"/>
	  </imageobject>
	  <textobject>
	    <phrase>Screenshot</phrase>
	  </textobject>
	</mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>

<para>
However, if there are damaged or missing source files then &kzen; can repair them if possible.
</para>

<para>
<screenshot>
<screeninfo>&kzen; after repairing damaged and missing source files</screeninfo>
	<mediaobject>
	  <imageobject>
	    <imagedata fileref="kzen_repaired.png" format="PNG"/>
	  </imageobject>
	  <textobject>
	    <phrase>Screenshot</phrase>
	  </textobject>
	</mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>

<para>
However, it is possible that there are either too many damaged and/or missing source files,
or not enough parity files to carry out a repair. In this case, &kzen; will report that it
is unable to carry out a repair of the source files. Your only recourse in this case will be
to either redownload the damaged and missing files, or download more parity files.
</para>

<para>
<screenshot>
<screeninfo>&kzen; is unable to repair the source files</screeninfo>
	<mediaobject>
	  <imageobject>
	    <imagedata fileref="kzen_repair_not_possible.png" format="PNG"/>
	  </imageobject>
	  <textobject>
	    <phrase>Screenshot</phrase>
	  </textobject>
	</mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>

</para>

</chapter>

