<appendix id="installation">

<title>Installation</title>

<sect1 id="getting-kzen">

<title>How to obtain &kzen;</title>

<para>
&kzen; can be found on <ulink url="http://kzen.googlecode.com">the &kzen; home page</ulink>.
</para>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="requirements">

<title>Requirements</title>

<para>
In order to successfully use &kzen; you need &kde; 3.5 and libmtp.
</para>

<para>
Libmtp can be obained from <ulink url="http://libmtp.sourceforge.net">the libmtp homepage</ulink>.
</para>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="compilation">

<title>Compilation and Installation</title>

<para>
In order to compile and install KZen on your system, type the following in the base directory of the KZen source:
</para>

<screen>
%cmake . -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX=$KDEDIR
%make
%make install
</screen>

</sect1>

<sect1 id="configuration">

<title>Configuration</title>

<para>
<screenshot>
<screeninfo>Here's a screenshot of &kzen;'s settings dialog</screeninfo>
	<mediaobject>
	  <imageobject>
	    <imagedata fileref="kzen_settings.png" format="PNG"/>
	  </imageobject>
	  <textobject>
	    <phrase>Screenshot</phrase>
	  </textobject>
	</mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>

<para>&kzen; allows the user to configure it to automatically verify the source files once the parity files are loaded.
Additionally, &kzen; can be configured to automatically repair any damaged source files if possible.
</para>

</sect1>

